# RunRush — Full Application Summary

## Overview

**RunRush** is a full-stack running/fitness tracker web app built with **Python/Flask** and **SQLite**. It lets users log runs, view stats & progress charts, earn achievement badges, compete on a weekly leaderboard, and sync offline-logged runs. An admin panel provides user management and platform-level analytics.

**Stack:** Flask 3.0 · SQLite · Jinja2 templates · Vanilla JS · CSS · Gunicorn (production)

---

## Database Schema (SQLite — [runs.db](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/runs.db))

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `users` | Accounts (username, PIN, display name, weight, height, weekly goal, theme, role, status, last login) |
| [runs](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/app.py#1257-1281) | Run entries (user_id, date, distance_km, time_min, pace, calories, created_at, insight) |
| [user_stats](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/app.py#410-456) | Aggregated stats per user (total distance, current/best streak) |
| [badges](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/app.py#1677-1740) | Badge definitions (key, name, description, icon, criteria type/value) |
| `user_badges` | Unlocked badges per user (badge_key, unlocked_at, activity_id) |
| `activity_logs` | Audit trail (user actions like login, run added, admin actions) |
| [edit_history](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/app.py#305-323) | Change history for edited runs (field, old value, new value) |
| `admin_notes` | Admin/moderator notes on users |

---

## Pages & Templates

| Page | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Landing** | `/` | Public marketing/landing page shown to unauthenticated users |
| **Login** | `/login` | Email + PIN authentication |
| **Register** | `/register` | New account creation |
| **Onboarding** | `/onboarding` | Post-registration setup (display name, weight, weekly goal) |
| **Dashboard** | `/dashboard` | Main app — stats, run history, charts, add run form, leaderboard |
| **Settings** | `/settings` | Profile editing (display name, weight, height, weekly goal, theme) |
| **Edit Run** | `/edit/<id>` | Edit a previously logged run (locked after 24h for regular users) |
| **Admin Panel** | `/admin` | User management, platform stats, activity logs |
| **403 Page** | — | Access denied page for non-admin users |

---

## Core Features

### 1. Run Logging & Stats
- Log runs with **date, distance (km), and time (min)** — pace & calories are auto-calculated.
- **Validation:** no future dates, positive values only, realistic pace range (2–30 min/km).
- **AI-style Insights:** each run gets a motivational insight comparing performance vs. recent history.
- **Run Locking:** runs older than 24 hours become read-only for regular users (admins can override).
- **Edit History:** all field changes are tracked in an audit table.

### 2. Dashboard Analytics
- **All-time stats:** total km, total calories, average pace.
- **Monthly stats:** same metrics scoped to current month.
- **Weekly goal progress:** configurable km target with progress bar.
- **Personal bests:** fastest 5K and 10K times.
- **Streak tracker:** current streak, best streak, and a weekly heatmap bar (🔥).
- **Sorting & Filtering:** by date / distance / time; filter by last 7 days, this month, or 5K/10K runs.

### 3. Progress Charts (API)
- `/api/progress-data` serves JSON chart data for **week**, **month**, or **year** ranges.
- Returns labels, data points, and computed stats (total, average, best, active days).

### 4. Achievement Badge System
- **Badge types:** Single Distance (5K, 10K), Accumulative Distance (50km, 100km), Streak (7-day, 30-day).
- Badges are evaluated automatically after each run is added.
- Newly unlocked badges are stored in the session for a celebration modal on the dashboard.
- **API endpoints:** `/api/badges` (full badge gallery with progress) and `/api/badges/progress` (compact stats).

### 5. Weekly Leaderboard
- Top 10 users by total distance for the current Mon–Sun week.
- Embedded in the dashboard.

### 6. Offline Sync
- Three JS modules handle offline capability:
  - [offline-storage.js](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/static/js/offline-storage.js) — LocalStorage-based run queue.
  - [sync-engine.js](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/static/js/sync-engine.js) — Syncs queued runs to `/api/sync-run` when back online.
  - [offline-ui.js](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/static/js/offline-ui.js) — UI indicators for offline status.
- **Data integrity:** SHA-256 hash verification on sync, duplicate detection server-side.

### 7. CSV Export
- `/export` downloads all of a user's runs as a `.csv` file.

### 8. User Settings
- Update profile (display name, weight, height), weekly goal, and theme (dark/light).
- **BMI calculation** displayed on dashboard if weight and height are set.
- **Account deletion** with full data cleanup (runs, stats, badges, logs).

---

## Admin Panel

- **Access:** restricted to users with [admin](file:///c:/Users/Yajat%20Sharma/Programming%20codes/Running-py/app.py#1449-1503) or `moderator` role.
- **Super Admin:** determined by `ADMIN_USER_ID` env variable (immutable, cannot be modified by other admins).
- **Capabilities:**

| Action | Admin | Moderator |
|---|---|---|
| View all users & logs | ✅ | ✅ |
| Block / Unblock users | ✅ | ✅ |
| Promote / Demote users | ✅ | ❌ |
| Delete users | ✅ | ❌ |

- **Platform stats:** total users, active users (last 7 days), total km across all users.
- **Activity logs:** last 20 actions (login, run added, admin actions, etc.).

---

## Auth System

- **PIN-based login** (username + numeric PIN, stored in plaintext — no hashing).
- **Session management** via Flask's built-in cookie sessions.
- Blocked users are rejected at login.
- `last_login` timestamp updated on each login.

